{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Bring back the death penalty",
        "additional_details": "The prison system is overcrowded and in some cases such as terrorism, prisons can be breeding grounds for radicalisation. There's also the cost of keeping a convicted criminal behind bars for years to consider as well as the victims of crime. We, as a nation should  show that we are tough on crime and tough on criminals as a deterrent to other potential criminals. Safety of the public is paramount.",
        "background": "The death penalty should be an option for convicted terrorists, mass murderers, serial rapists, paedophiles and child killers. Only one appeal should be allowed, with no right to legal aid, which must be lodged and heard within 3 months of conviction.",
